hilosophy and Theology”, “The Language of Religious Experience and Leading a Christian Life”.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexDialects. 0aGodxHistory of doctrines. 4aChristentum. 4aGeschichtstheologie. 4aHistoriographie. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aSpätantike. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aChristianity.  aChurch History.  aHistoriography.  aLate Antiquity.  aTheology of History.1 aFrost, Stefanie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMennecke, Ute, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2009z9783110219494oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311020553440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311021125240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110211252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110211252/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2009  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014